{
  "stem": "18670.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We would march in circle in a courtyard with other prisoners, Belgium refugees, Belgian people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember even like today they would holler at us, [FRENCH], and tell us we couldn't talk.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they called my name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I-- at that time, I made up my mind to whether I'm going to change my name, because they couldn't pronounce my name.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They would say, 'Monsieur Scotts-care, Scotts-care.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it came out very funny the way they said it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I said, well, I got to change the name, because nobody can pronounce this German name.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, when we handed those questionnaires, I started thinking, how can I become a political refugee?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And well, I-- I've been lucky all my life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had an uncle, my father's youngest brother, even though my grandfather was a rabbi, was a Communist from way back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had graduated from the University of Vienna as a lawyer, international law, one of the youngest graduates.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At the age of 21, he graduated with a law degree.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And during the height of the Depression, he spoke several languages.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he learned Russian in a hurry.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was an opening for a editor for the international paper.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he became the foreign editor-- editor of the in Moscow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And after five years being in Russia, he came back and became the editor of the Rotes Wein, which was the Daily Worker, the Communist paper in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he also defended some Communists in court.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I realized that I put down that this uncle of mine, the Communist, is endangering us too, because we have to go back to Germany, the Germans, the Nazis in particular, don't recognize that you could be innocent, guilty by relationship, guilty by association.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we all know that this is possible.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
